    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-12T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your Number 1715 of November 10<note n="72" xml:id="d626fn72">Not printed.</note>
                    and Department’s December 15, 6 p.m.<note n="73" xml:id="d626fn73">See footnote
                        66, <ref target="#pg_644">p. 644</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The American Government considers it important that land frontier tariff as well
                    as maritime should be revised otherwise sea-borne commerce under increased rates
                    will be at additional disadvantage. A failure to revise the land frontier tariff
                    may endanger the acceptance of the revised maritime tariff. At present the lack
                    of a recognized Government in Russia makes it impossible to discuss the question
                    with Petrograd, but you are instructed to bring the American views to the
                    attention of the Chinese Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
